Blocking critics on Facebook: Don't stand for public office if you can't stand criticism
Our country’s father knew what was bad publicity.
The Americans loved George Washington, but the newspapers soon began to criticise him for all possible domestic policies, all the way to his political principles.
Criticism certainly annoyed me,
But he did not silence his critics.
If freedom of speech is lifted, we may be led as stupid and silent as sheep for slaughter,” Washington said in 1783.
That’s where we get to the governor of Maryland, Larry Hogan, who should learn from Washington.
Hogan's staff have removed at least 450 comments from his official Facebook page and blocked their authors.
